1 2. Upon written request, the superintendent of public instruction may allow a school
2 district annually to select courses other than economics or problems of democracy for
3 purposes of exposing students to the concepts of personal finance, as listed in this
4 section, provided the school district can demonstrate that the number of students
5 exposed to the concepts in the other selected courses would meet or exceed the
6 number of students exposed under the requirements of subsection 1.
7 3. The requirements of this section may be provided by the regular classroom teacher of
8 the course in which the concepts of personal finance are incorporated.
